00:15:30,574 --> 00:15:32,121
And trace their location.

256
00:15:32,473 --> 00:15:34,364
No. Sorry, that's not possible.

257
00:15:34,477 --> 00:15:37,625
The ISPs aren't going to give
out a player's real‐life info.

258
00:15:37,652 --> 00:15:39,616
If all we have to go on are their handles.

259
00:15:39,902 --> 00:15:42,794
Maybe if we ask the game's admins, they could help.

260
00:15:42,842 --> 00:15:47,574
They might, but GGO's admins are in the US,
so it'll be a while before we got an answer.

261
00:15:49,748 --> 00:15:51,059
I know my brother,

262
00:15:51,413 --> 00:15:54,465
And right now, he's risking his life in that game,

263
00:15:54,490 --> 00:15:56,707
Trying to find out who this person is.

264
00:15:57,104 --> 00:16:00,012
When he came home last night,
he had this look on his face,

265
00:16:00,125 --> 00:16:01,585
Like he'd seen a ghost.

266
00:16:02,335 --> 00:16:05,740
He must have bumped into the
guy yesterday during the prelims.

267
00:16:06,186 --> 00:16:10,629
I bet that's when he realized someone
from Laughing Coffin was in "GGO",

268
00:16:11,615 --> 00:16:14,621
Someone who figured out how
to kill players for real again.

269
00:16:15,865 --> 00:16:18,651
My brother went back to put an end to that nightmare,

270
00:16:19,288 --> 00:16:22,788
to find out his name, and stop his PKing once and for all.

271
00:16:23,959 --> 00:16:25,240
Darn it, Kirito.

272
00:16:25,408 --> 00:16:27,073
You should have said something.

273
00:16:27,451 --> 00:16:30,345
Why? Why do you always do this?

274
00:16:31,558 --> 00:16:32,909
That damn idiot!

275
00:16:33,067 --> 00:16:34,575
Why didn't he say anything?

276
00:16:34,742 --> 00:16:39,488
I could be backing him up right now, all he had
to do was ask, and I would have converted over, too.

277
00:16:39,534 --> 00:16:40,649
We all would have.

278
00:16:41,194 --> 00:16:43,704
Don't you see? That's why he didn't tell us.

279
00:16:43,926 --> 00:16:46,891
If he thought there was any
real danger in what he was doing,

280
00:16:46,916 --> 00:16:49,355
there's no way he'd get us mixed up in it, too.

281
00:16:49,644 --> 00:16:51,075
That's just how he is.

282
00:16:51,554 --> 00:16:52,625
Yeah, you're right.

283
00:16:52,906 --> 00:16:55,143
He always thinks of others before himself.

284
00:16:55,322 --> 00:16:57,914
In fact, he's probably protecting someone right now,

285
00:16:57,953 --> 00:17:01,310
and whoever that is, I bet it's
someone who doesn't like him much.

286
00:17:06,571 --> 00:17:09,609
Okay, Chrysheight, where is Kirito diving from?

287
00:17:09,692 --> 00:17:12,062
I know you know, so you better tell me now.

288
00:17:12,193 --> 00:17:12,524
Mm...

289
00:17:12,687 --> 00:17:15,305
That's confidential.

290
00:17:16,418 --> 00:17:19,151
Eh, okay, okay. I'll tell you.

291
00:17:19,564 --> 00:17:21,707
I set up the room myself, so he's safe.

292
00:17:21,732 --> 00:17:24,796
Security's rock‐solid, and
the monitoring's top of the line.

293
00:17:25,136 --> 00:17:28,035
I've got a trained professional
right by his side at all times,

294
00:17:28,059 --> 00:17:30,810
and I guarantee that his body's in no danger whatsoever.

295
00:17:30,835 --> 00:17:31,868
Where is he?!

296
00:17:32,679 --> 00:17:33,720
A hospital.

297
00:17:33,885 --> 00:17:36,548
It's in Ochanomizu in Chiyoda ward.

298
00:17:36,573 --> 00:17:37,672
He's in Chiyoda?

299
00:17:38,283 --> 00:17:41,595
Wait. Is that the same hospital
he was in during his rehabilitation?

300
00:17:41,620 --> 00:17:43,215
Yes, that's the one.

301
00:17:43,568 --> 00:17:47,414
I'm going over there. I want to see
him, and you can't do a thing about it.

302
00:17:54,825 --> 00:17:56,327
Tell me you got a plan.

303
00:17:57,627 --> 00:17:59,326
We're going to take out Death Gun.

304
00:17:59,708 --> 00:18:00,763
Once we do,

305
00:18:00,974 --> 00:18:03,285
His real world partner'll stand down.

306
00:18:03,468 --> 00:18:05,502
Then he'll just leave your apartment.

307
00:18:06,002 --> 00:18:08,037
Okay, but he's skilled,

308
00:18:08,182 --> 00:18:10,415
Black Star or no Black Star.

309
00:18:11,075 --> 00:18:15,270
You saw. He dodged Hecate's
bullet from just 100 meters away.

310
00:18:16,341 --> 00:18:20,111
And besides, I can't hide in this cave forever, you know.

311
00:18:20,635 --> 00:18:24,338
By now, the other players probably
figured out the two of us are in here.

312
00:18:24,511 --> 00:18:26,388
We might as well be sitting ducks.

313
00:18:26,668 --> 00:18:30,001
It's just a matter of time
before someone tosses a grenade in.

314
00:18:30,247 --> 00:18:31,154
You're right.

315
00:18:31,501 --> 00:18:34,160
We've been a team this whole time anyway, right?

316
00:18:34,718 --> 00:18:36,477
Might as well finish it together.

317
00:18:36,737 --> 00:18:37,692
Okay,

318
00:18:37,717 --> 00:18:40,787
But there's still the risk he shoots you with that gun.

319
00:18:41,147 --> 00:18:42,309
Oh, that thing.

320
00:18:42,494 --> 00:18:44,979
It's just an old‐school single‐action sidearm.

321
00:18:45,336 --> 00:18:48,291
He can fire it all he wants, but I got you there.

322
00:18:48,612 --> 00:18:50,420
Just deflect the bullets with your sword.

323
00:18:50,640 --> 00:18:53,450
Right, and I won't let a single one of 'em hit you.

324
00:18:53,856 --> 00:18:56,487
I still don't feel good about you being out there, though.

325
00:18:56,790 --> 00:18:59,976
I mean, Death Gun's dangerous, and
you shouldn't get too close to him.

326
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:01,652
Oh, come on.

327
00:19:01,712 --> 00:19:06,389
Hang on. I'm totally cool with you fighting
with me, and I wouldn't have it any other way,

328
00:19:06,840 --> 00:19:09,451
But, Sinon, you're a sniper, remember?

329
00:19:09,661 --> 00:19:11,887
Isn't your specialty the long‐range attack?

330
00:19:12,145 --> 00:19:14,022
Well, yeah. What about it?

331
00:19:14,459 --> 00:19:15,517
Here's the plan.

332
00:19:15,736 --> 00:19:18,929
On the next scan, I'm gonna
step outside so it picks me up.

333
00:19:19,088 --> 00:19:21,350
That way, we'll get Death Gun to come to us.

334
00:19:21,702 --> 00:19:23,925
He'll probably keep his distance and take cover.

335
00:19:24,207 --> 00:19:26,354
Then he'll try to pick me off with his rifle.

336
00:19:26,706 --> 00:19:30,257
When he shoots, we'll know where
he is, and then you take him out.

337
00:19:30,362 --> 00:19:31,487
What do you think?

338
00:19:31,539 --> 00:19:33,787
Are you cool with playing the decoy?

339
00:19:33,967 --> 00:19:34,567
Mm‐hmm.

340
00:19:35,346 --> 00:19:37,770
All right. We do it your way then.

341
00:19:38,040 --> 00:19:41,309
Just be careful out there, 'cause
if he drops you with his first shot,

342
00:19:41,334 --> 00:19:42,662
I'm gonna be pissed.

343
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:45,328
Heh. I'll keep that in mind.

344
00:19:45,749 --> 00:19:47,454
Wait. I just remembered.

345
00:19:47,556 --> 00:19:51,250
His rifle's got a silencer, and you
won't see the bullet line on the first shot.

346
00:19:51,420 --> 00:19:53,601
Oh, I'll just predict the prediction,

347
00:19:53,882 --> 00:19:56,438
You know, like a certain no‐good faker told...

348
00:19:56,828 --> 00:19:59,664
Um, I think we should stop talking.

349
00:19:59,830 --> 00:20:00,497
Uh...

350
00:20:04,034 --> 00:20:05,884
Ugh. Oh, crap.

351
00:20:05,909 --> 00:20:07,809
We should have been paying more attention.

352
00:20:08,115 --> 00:20:09,027
What is it?

353
00:20:09,306 --> 00:20:10,965
And will it kill us?

354
00:20:11,043 --> 00:20:13,002
It's a live‐stream camera.

355
00:20:13,095 --> 00:20:14,960
Usually they're only supposed to shadow.

356
00:20:14,985 --> 00:20:16,532
Players on the battlefield.

357
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:20,510
I guess this one's in here now 'cause
there aren't many of us left out there.

358
00:20:20,583 --> 00:20:22,067
Then do you...

359
00:20:22,243 --> 00:20:23,536
Think it heard us?

360
00:20:23,695 --> 00:20:25,863
Not a chance. For it to pick us up,

361
00:20:25,914 --> 00:20:28,353
We'd have to be shouting at the top of our lungs.

362
00:20:28,602 --> 00:20:30,219
Wave to the audience.

363
00:20:30,268 --> 00:20:32,940
Unless you got someone back at home.

364
00:20:32,987 --> 00:20:34,494
You don't want seeing this.

365
00:20:35,430 --> 00:20:37,446
Uh, I, um...

366
00:20:38,680 --> 00:20:40,778
Shouldn't you be worried who's watching?

367
00:20:40,905 --> 00:20:45,452
I mean, since I sort of look like a girl,
they might, you know, think you're, you know.

368
00:20:46,638 --> 00:20:48,809
I don't care. They can think what they want.

369
00:20:48,966 --> 00:20:51,566
The guys in this game are dorks. If they think I'm gay,

370
00:20:51,628 --> 00:20:54,403
at least they'll stop hitting on me every five seconds.

371
00:20:54,649 --> 00:20:57,564
How much longer am I gonna have
to keep pretending to be a girl?

372
00:20:57,589 --> 00:20:59,252
Oh, you poor baby.

373
00:20:59,277 --> 00:21:03,862
You've been faking it like a champ since you
logged in. Another hour or two won't matter.

374
00:21:04,445 --> 00:21:05,376
Thank god.

375
00:21:08,172 --> 00:21:09,516
We better get ready.

376
00:21:10,579 --> 00:21:13,104
We got two minutes before the next sat scan.

377
00:21:13,374 --> 00:21:14,592
I'll set up here.

378
00:21:14,762 --> 00:21:17,264
When you get outside, fire up your terminal,

379
00:21:17,306 --> 00:21:19,338
and let me know when our boy's close.

380
00:21:23,212 --> 00:21:24,812
Wait. Hold on.

381
00:21:25,265 --> 00:21:26,683
Why? What's wrong?

382
00:21:27,078 --> 00:21:29,291
It's too late to change the plan now.

383
00:21:29,708 --> 00:21:31,983
No, I don't want to change anything.

384
00:21:32,310 --> 00:21:33,633
It's something else.

385
00:21:33,896 --> 00:21:36,878
I was just thinking about Death Gun's real handle here.

386
00:21:36,982 --> 00:21:40,321
The only name you didn't recognize
who's still alive is Sterben.

387
00:21:40,410 --> 00:21:41,661
Oh. Huh.

388
00:21:42,083 --> 00:21:43,338
I guess that's him then.

389
00:21:44,018 --> 00:21:46,394
I wonder why he gave himself that name, though.

390
00:21:47,288 --> 00:21:48,949
If I get up close and personal,

391
00:21:49,043 --> 00:21:50,709
I'll be sure to ask him for you.

392
00:21:53,076 --> 00:21:54,845
Well, here goes nothing.

393
00:21:57,729 --> 00:21:59,048
Be careful, okay?

394
00:23:35,967 --> 00:23:38,387
Next time: "Bullet of a Phantom".

